This paper discusses research collaboration and citation impact across different fields and countries. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-categories are likely to be those related to information retrieval (cs.IR), digital libraries (cs.DL), social networks (cs.SI), software engineering (cs.SE), and cybersecurity (cs.CY). These sub-categories are relevant because they involve collaboration and citation impact, and the study's findings could be applicable to these fields. The sub-category of systems and databases (cs.SD) is also relevant as it involves team size and collaboration.
